  "description": [
    "Roosevelt Is Said to Have Hinted Support for New York Race Within the last week President Roosevelt has indicated he believes Postmaster General Parley is entitled to the Democratic gubernatorial nom ination in New York next fall it was learned yesterday from a trustworthy source The President it was said had told Mr Farley he would like to see him in the Governors man lion at Albany Mention of the incident caused a ttir among the New Deal backers of Robert H Jackson spearhead of the administrations trustbusting drive who had assumed the Assistant Attor ney General was the White House candidate for the New York nomina tion Many of the Jackson supporters refused to believe the President has said what he is reported to have said to Mr Farley Others thought the indorsement if given was not to be taken at face value If Mr Farley indicated he wanted the nomination which this group doubted the President it was argued could not very well say no Neverthe less the Jackson supporters declined to be shaken in their belief that Mr Jackson was the Presidents man President Not Committed No one close to the White House has ever committed the"
